            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "So I found this:\r\nThis line in the [terminal.c](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/terminal.c#L384) file apparently disables some options from the current window when entering a terminal.\r\nAs I found, \"w_p_cul\" is the cursor line, \"w_p_cuc\" is the cursor column, and \"w_p_rnu\" is the relative number.\r\n\r\nMaybe this has nothing to do with it. If you could guide me a bit more I would be glad to help with this.",
